Conservative MP David Amess has died after he was stabbed multiple times at a church in his constituency. Amess, the MP for Southend West, was holding a surgery with constituents at Belfairs Methodist Church in Leigh-on-Sea on Friday. Following the incident Essex police said it had been called to reports of a stabbing in Eastwood Road North shortly after 12.05pm. A man has been arrested and the police are not looking for anyone else in connection with the incident. This is a breaking news story and will be updated. Follow HuffPost UK on Twitter, Facebook and Instagram.